{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T09:23:23.270Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Loss Scaling — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Loss Scaling Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a technique in mixed precision training where the loss function is multiplied by a constant factor (scaling factor) before backpropagation to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "prevent small gradients from underflowing to zero"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in FP16."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Unscaled loss\nloss = model(input)\n\n# Scaled loss (multiply by k)\nscaled_loss = loss * loss_scale  # e.g., loss_scale = 1024 [web:263]\nscaled_loss.backward()  # Backpropagate with scaled loss [web:263]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Loss Scaling Matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss scaling is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "essential for FP16 mixed precision training"}, {"type": "text", "text": " because FP16 has a limited dynamic range (6e-8 to 65504)."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Underflow Problem"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "FP16-to-FP32 conversion (backward pass):\nSmall gradient (1e-10) → FP16 → Underflows to 0\n\nResult: Gradient vanishes, training stalls"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When gradients undergo FP32-to-FP16 conversion during backpropagation, most small values result in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "0s in FP16"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", causing training to diverge."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Loss Scaling Solves It"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scale up loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": " before backpropagation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradients become larger"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (shifted into FP16 range)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Unscale gradients"}, {"type": "text", "text": " before weight update to maintain correct magnitude"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mathematical equivalence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\n\\frac{\\partial (k \\mathcal{L})}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} = k \\frac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}}\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "k"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the scaling factor."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss scaling is essentially an "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "implementation of gradient scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Loss Scaling Works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Complete Pipeline"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Forward pass (FP16)\n   loss = model(input)\n\n2. Scale loss\n   scaled_loss = loss * loss_scale  # e.g., 1024 [web:263]\n\n3. Backward pass (gradients in FP16)\n   scaled_loss.backward()\n   # Gradients underflow if unscaled, but stay representable if scaled [web:263]\n\n4. Unscale gradients (FP32)\n   optimizer.step(grad_scale=loss_scale)  # Divide by loss_scale [web:264]\n\n5. Weight update (FP32)\n   Parameters updated in FP32 (master weights) [web:264]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Static vs Dynamic Loss Scaling"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Static Loss Scaling"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Definition"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Use a fixed scaling factor (e.g., 1024) for entire training"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The loss scale value becomes a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "hyperparameter that needs per-model tuning"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Issues"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Single scale cannot adapt to different layers at different training stages\n- Requires experimentation to find correct loss scale\n- May be too small (underflow) or too large (overflow)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dynamic Loss Scaling"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Definition"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Automatically adjusts the scale factor during training"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "How it works"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Start"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with initial scale (e.g., 1024 or 2e15)\n2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Increase"}, {"type": "text", "text": " by 2x periodically if no overflow detected\n3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Halve"}, {"type": "text", "text": " immediately on NaN/Inf detection\n4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adapts"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to gradient magnitude changes throughout training"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PyTorch implementation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (GradScaler):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\n\nscaler = torch.cuda.amp.GradScaler()  # Exponential backoff [web:263]\n\nfor input, target in dataset:\n    with torch.cuda.amp.autocast(dtype=torch.float16):\n        output = model(input)\n        loss = compute_loss(output, target)\n    \n    # Scale loss\n    scaler.scale(loss).backward()\n    \n    # Unscaled optimizer step\n    scaler.step(optimizer)\n    \n    # Update scaler (adjust scale)\n    scaler.update()  # Exponential backoff [web:263]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PyTorch uses exponential backoff"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to automatically adjust the scale factor, periodically increasing it and decreasing on NaN detection."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adaptive Loss Scaling"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Advanced technique"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Introduce "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "layer-wise loss scale values"}, {"type": "text", "text": " automatically computed during training."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Benefits"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Removes need"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to tune model-specific loss scale hyperparameter\n- Each layer gets its own scale, adapting to its specific gradient magnitude\n- Shortens convergence time and improves accuracy"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "FP16 vs BF16 Loss Scaling"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "FP16 Loss Scaling"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Required"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Loss scaling is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "necessary"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for FP16"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reason"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": FP16's 5-bit exponent range (6e-8 to 65504) causes small gradients to underflow"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "BF16 Loss Scaling"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not required"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": BF16 "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "eliminates most underflow issues"}, {"type": "text", "text": " without loss scaling"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reason"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": BF16's 8-bit exponent range (1e-38 to 3e38) matches FP32, preventing underflow"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typical Scaling Factors"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scenario"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scaling Factor"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Notes"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Initial"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1024"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Start moderate"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PyTorch default"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dynamically adjusts"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Auto-tuned"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cerebras max"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2e15"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Maximum allowed"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cerebras min"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2e-14"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Minimum threshold"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Post-overflow"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "512"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Halve after NaN"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PyTorch Implementation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using GradScaler (Automatic Dynamic Scaling)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\n\nmodel = MyModel().float()  # Load in FP32 [web:254]\noptimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters())\nscaler = torch.cuda.amp.GradScaler()  # Automatic dynamic scaling [web:263]\n\nfor input, target in dataset:\n    input = input.to('cuda')\n    target = target.to('cuda')\n    \n    # Forward pass in FP16\n    with torch.cuda.amp.autocast(dtype=torch.float16):\n        output = model(input)\n        loss = compute_loss(output, target)\n    \n    # Backward with scaling\n    scaler.scale(loss).backward()\n    \n    # Unscaled optimizer step\n    scaler.step(optimizer)\n    \n    # Update scaler (adjust scale automatically)\n    scaler.update()  # Exponential backoff [web:263]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Manual Loss Scaling"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Manual scaling (not recommended)\nloss_scale = 1024\n\nfor input, target in dataset:\n    with torch.cuda.amp.autocast(dtype=torch.float16):\n        output = model(input)\n        loss = compute_loss(output, target) * loss_scale  # Manual scale [web:263]\n    \n    loss.backward()\n    optimizer.step()"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TensorFlow Implementation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using Dynamic Loss Scaling"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import tensorflow as tf\n\n# Enable mixed precision with FP16\npolicy = tf.keras.mixed_precision.Policy('mixed_float16')\ntf.keras.mixed_precision.set_global_policy(policy)\n\n# Dynamic loss scaling (Cerebras)\nfrom cbtorch.amp import GradScaler  # Dynamic loss scaling [web:264]\n\nscaler = GradScaler(\n    initial_loss_scale=2e15,  # Default max [web:264]\n    min_loss_scale=2e-14      # Default min [web:264]\n)\n\n# Training\nfor input, target in dataset:\n    with tf.device('GPU'):\n        loss = model(input, training=True)\n    \n    # Scale loss before backward\n    scaled_loss = scaler.scale(loss)\n    scaled_loss.backward()\n    \n    # Unscaled optimizer step\n    scaler.step(optimizer)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Loss Scaling"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Loss Scaling When:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training with FP16"}, {"type": "text", "text": " mixed precision"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradients underflow to zero"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in FP16"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not using BF16"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (which doesn't need scaling)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Don't Use Loss Scaling When:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Using BF16"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (BF16 doesn't require scaling)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Full precision FP32"}, {"type": "text", "text": " training (no scaling needed)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best Practices"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Use Dynamic Loss Scaling"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Always use automatic scaling (GradScaler in PyTorch)\nReason: No need to tune hyperparameter, adapts during training"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Monitor for NaN/Inf"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Check for overflow detection\nif torch.isnan(loss) or torch.isinf(loss):\n    scaler.update()  # Automatically halves scale [web:263]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Start with Moderate Scale"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Initial scale: 1024 (PyTorch default)\nAvoid too large (2e15) which may cause immediate overflow"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. Keep FP32 Master Weights"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "model = MyModel().float()  # Must be FP32 for mixed precision [web:254]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of loss scaling as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "zooming in on a microscope"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small object"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (gradient): Too tiny to see (underflows to 0)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Zoom in"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (scale loss): Makes object larger (gradients shift to representable range)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Take measurement"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (backprop): Record gradient at larger scale"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Zoom out"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (unscale): Divide measurement by scale factor to get original size"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use measurement"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Apply corrected gradient to update weights"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Multiply loss by constant factor before backpropagation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scaled loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "k \\mathcal{L}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " where "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "k"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is scaling factor"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Purpose"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Prevent gradients from underflowing to zero in FP16"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Underflow"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Small gradients (1e-10) → FP16 → 0"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Solution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Scale up gradients into FP16 representable range"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Unscale"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Divide gradients by loss scale before weight update"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Mathematically equivalent to loss scaling"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Static scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Fixed factor (e.g., 1024)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem static"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Requires per-model hyperparameter tuning"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dynamic scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Automatically adjusts during training"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PyTorch GradScaler"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Auto-adjusts via exponential backoff"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Increase scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": 2x periodically if no overflow"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Decrease scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Halve immediately on NaN/Inf"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adaptive scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Layer-wise scales computed during training"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Initial scale"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": 1024 (PyTorch default) or 2e15 (Cerebras max)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "FP16"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Requires"}, {"type": "text", "text": " loss scaling (5-bit exponent, limited range